Package: gravitr
Title: Gravity-Based Allocation Models
Version: 0.9
Authors@R: c(
    person("Hugo", "Perilleux", email = "hugoperilleux@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Pierre", "Marissal", role = c("aut")))
Description: An R package for gravity-model allocation of supply and demand
    using the Furness convergence algorithm. The package supports the analysis
    of spatial accessibility to public services and facilities such as
    childcare, education, healthcare, sports facilities, and other collective
    amenities. By accounting for both travel distance and competition for
    limited resources, it helps identify spatial inequalities in access and
    evaluate the balance between local demand and available supply.
